This paper is about improving the performance of automatic speech translation (AST) models using data augmentation and pretraining techniques. The paper focuses on comparing different approaches on the same datasets, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and speech processing. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SD (Sound) and cs.LG (Learning) as likely options. Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as data augmentation and pretraining, which are common in machine learning research, suggesting the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
